<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
{{> head}}
<body>
    <header>
        {{> nav nav}}
    </header>
    <main class="haikus">
        <h1>@EverydayHaikus</h1>
        <p>A twitter robot delivering a daily dose of Haikus, right in your timeline!</p>
        <article class="haikus_content">
            <h2>Quick facts</h2>
            <ul>
                <li class="content_li">The code lives in Github (<a href="https://github.com/garancev/twitterbot-haikus">go to haikuEveryday github repo</a>).</li>
                <li class="content_li">The code is uploaded online on <a href="https://heroku.com">Heroku</a>.</li>
                <li class="content_li">All the haikus live in a postgreSQL database.</li>
                <li class="content_li">It is scheduled to tweet every day at 9.30 AM. </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Why Heroku ?</h2>
            Amongst others, this
            <a href="https://medium.com/@mattpopovich/how-to-build-and-deploy-a-simple-twitter-bot-super-fast-with-node-js-and-heroku-7b322dbb5dd3"> short tutorial by Matt Popovich</a> convinced me to used Heroku, due to the scheduler plugin. I took the opportunity to also create the database over there, within the same app.
        </article>

        {{> twitter}}
    </main>

    {{> footer footer}}
</body>
</html>